<%# Phase 29 (settings refactor) — security pane (row 1 right).
    Phase 32 follow-up (2026-05-16) — 2FA / TOTP cleanup.
    Post-Phase-25 rollback — the auto-block list + locations modal
    launcher were removed along with the new-location approval
    surface.

    2026-05-16 (sessions revamp v2):

      * The "2FA: on / active sessions: N" helper copy + the
        "active sessions open in a modal." / "the direct link still
        works for JS-off clients." prose are gone — 2FA is mandatory
        (the gate forces enrollment), session counts and modal-vs-
        direct framing are noise.
      * The `[ sessions ]` modal launcher is gone. The sessions table
        renders INLINE inside this pane.
      * The `[ 2FA / TOTP ]` launcher was already dropped — the
        surface it opened (manage + disable + backup-code rotation)
        moved to operator rake tasks. 2FA enrollment itself is
        forced via the mandatory-2FA gate's auto-open modal on
        `/settings?enroll_totp=1`.

    2026-05-16 (sessions revamp v3 — modal-confirm):

      * The standalone `/settings/sessions/revokes/:ids` action-screen
        confirmation page is GONE. Bulk revoke now opens an in-page
        `<dialog>` confirm modal mounted at the bottom of this pane,
        following the same convention as the reindex modal in
        `_stack_pane.html.erb` (page-level mount keeps the CSRF token
        bound to the current session; `form_with` ensures the hidden
        `authenticity_token` is valid). The `sessions-bulk-revoke`
        Stimulus controller is extended to populate the modal's
        title text, conditional warning, and form `action` at click
        time — the modal is one shared instance, content is dynamic
        based on the current checkbox selection. %>
<div class="pane">
  <fieldset style="padding: 8px;" data-controller="sessions-bulk-revoke">
    <legend><h2><%= t("settings.security.heading") %></h2></legend>

    <%= render(Sessions::TableComponent.new(
      sessions: @sessions,
      sessions_sort: @sessions_sort,
      sessions_dir: @sessions_dir,
      current_session_id: Current.session&.id
    )) %>

    <%# Revoke-sessions confirm modal (2026-05-16 revamp v3).

        One shared `<dialog>` mounted at the pane level. The
        `sessions-bulk-revoke` Stimulus controller populates the
        title (`revoke N session(s)?`), the conditional warning
        (`this set includes your current session. revoking it signs
        you out.`), and the form `action` attribute at click time
        based on the current checkbox selection.

        Page-level mount mirrors the reindex modal in
        `_stack_pane.html.erb` — the hidden `authenticity_token`
        baked by `form_with` is rendered in a real request context
        with a session-bound CSRF token, so submitting from the
        modal never trips `InvalidAuthenticityToken`. (A
        broadcast-driven render in a job context has no `request` /
        `session` and would bake an unbound token — same hazard
        called out in `_voyage_section.html.erb`.)

        The form `action` carries a literal `0` ids segment at render
        time (the route constraint `[0-9,]+` requires a digit, and
        `0` is filtered out by `parse_ids` server-side as a safety
        net — so a hand-crafted POST to the placeholder URL is a
        no-op). Stimulus rewrites the segment to
        `/settings/sessions/revokes/<real-ids>` when the modal opens.
        The hidden `confirm=yes` param mirrors what the deleted
        action-screen used to submit; `BulkRevokesController#create`
        still gates on it. %>
    <% if @sessions.any? %>
      <%= render(Sessions::BulkRevokeModalComponent.new) %>
    <% end %>
  </fieldset>
</div>
